all joys in this life

1749
01:32:39,554 --> 01:32:41,722
"to help maintain
this government

1750
01:32:42,256 --> 01:32:45,509
"and to pay that debt.

1751
01:32:45,509 --> 01:32:50,348
"sarah, my love for you
is deathless.

1752
01:32:50,348 --> 01:32:52,516
"it seems to bind me
with mighty cables

1753
01:32:53,067 --> 01:32:55,770
"that nothing but
omnipotence can break,

1754
01:32:55,770 --> 01:32:57,405
"and yet my love
of country

1755
01:32:57,405 --> 01:32:59,574
"comes over me
like a strong wind,

1756
01:33:00,107 --> 01:33:06,080
"and bears me irresistibly
with all those chains
to the battlefield.

1757
01:33:06,080 --> 01:33:08,783
"the memory of all
the blissful moments
i have enjoyed with you

1758
01:33:08,783 --> 01:33:11,502
"come crowding over me,

1759
01:33:11,502 --> 01:33:15,289
"and i feel
most deeply grateful
to god and you

1760
01:33:15,289 --> 01:33:18,509
"that i've enjoyed them
for so long.

1761
01:33:19,060 --> 01:33:20,678
"and how hard it is
for me to give them up

1762
01:33:21,212 --> 01:33:25,549
"and burn to ashes
the hopes of future years,

1763
01:33:25,549 --> 01:33:29,353
"when, god willing,
we might still have
lived and loved together,

1764
01:33:29,353 --> 01:33:33,691
"and see our boys
grown up to honorable
manhood around us.

1765
01:33:33,691 --> 01:33:38,980
"if i do not return,
my dear sarah,

1766
01:33:38,980 --> 01:33:42,233
"never forget
how much i loved you,

1767
01:33:42,233 --> 01:33:47,121
"nor that when
my last breath escapes me
on the battlefield,

1768
01:33:47,121 --> 01:33:50,374
"it will whisper your name.

1769
01:33:50,374 --> 01:33:53,628
"forgive my many faults

1770
01:33:53,628 --> 01:33:57,415
"and the many pains
i have caused you.

1771
01:33:57,415 --> 01:34:01,752
"how thoughtless,
how foolish i have
sometimes been.

1772
01:34:02,837 --> 01:34:04,472
"but, oh, sarah,

1773
01:34:04,472 --> 01:34:07,725
"if the dead can
come back to this earth

1774
01:34:07,725 --> 01:34:10,978
"and flit unseen
around those they love,

1775
01:34:10,978 --> 01:34:12,596
"i shall always be
with you

1776
01:34:12,596 --> 01:34:14,765
"in the brightest day
and the darkest night.

1777
01:34:14,765 --> 01:34:16,400
"always.

1778
01:34:16,934 --> 01:34:18,569
"always.

1779
01:34:20,187 --> 01:34:23,441
"and when the soft breeze
fans your cheek,

1780
01:34:23,441 --> 01:34:25,609
"it shall be my breath.

1781
01:34:25,609 --> 01:34:28,329
"or the cool air
at your throbbing temple,

1782
01:34:28,329 --> 01:34:31,582
"it shall be
my spirit passing by.

1783
01:34:34,251 --> 01:34:38,039
"sarah, do not
mourn me dead.

1784
01:34:38,039 --> 01:34:40,758
"think i am gone

1785
01:34:40,758 --> 01:34:42,927
"and wait for me,

1786
01:34:42,927 --> 01:34:45,096
for we shall meet again."

1787
01:34:51,052 --> 01:34:53,771
sullivan ballou
was killed a week later

1788
01:34:53,771 --> 01:34:57,024
at the first battle
of bull run.

